{
  "_comment": [
    "B1 — declarative model-selection policy for the LLM gateway.",
    "Copy to llm-policy.json and set GATEWAY_MODEL_POLICY_ENABLED=true to activate.",
    "While that flag is false this file is never read and routing is unchanged.",
    "",
    "The alias strings in `tiers` are catalog ids from llm-models.json, NOT raw",
    "provider model names. Tiers are LISTS: resolution walks down them and takes",
    "the first alias whose provider is ready, so a missing credential costs you",
    "the second entry instead of a 503.",
    "",
    "Route matching: most-specific `when` wins (by count of matched keys); ties",
    "break by the order routes appear in this file. `when` may only contain",
    "task_tag, stage and purpose — a route naming any other key is DROPPED with a",
    "warning rather than silently matching more broadly than you wrote it.",
    "",
    "escalateWhenInputTokensExceed moves the chosen tier up exactly ONE rung",
    "(cheap -> standard -> deep) when the estimated input exceeds the threshold.",
    "That estimate is chars/4 over the request messages. It is the only automatic",
    "signal here, and it exists because 'distill a README' and 'distill a 200-file",
    "repo' arrive under the same task_tag and only one belongs on a cheap model.",
    "",
    "Everything else is a rule you wrote down. There is deliberately no cost or",
    "latency optimizer and no quality-based escalation: this platform has no",
    "quality signal to tune against, so such a router would be fitting noise.",
    "",
    "The three agent_turn/stage routes below were migrated out of",
    "WORKBENCH_DEFAULT_STAGE_MODEL_ALIASES — a built-in {stageKey: alias} map in",
    "blueprint.router.ts, overridable by an env var holding JSON. That is a",
    "routing rule, and it was expressed as a caller-side alias PIN, which this",
    "gateway treats as a hard pin and skips policy for entirely. So while that",
    "map was applied at launch, workbench traffic could not be routed at all.",
    "The rule is preserved as written — code-heavy stages get a stronger model",
    "than the agent_turn default — but the model is now named by TIER, so the",
    "absolute choice follows the tier table above rather than a frozen alias.",
    "Changing it is a policy edit, not a redeploy plus a relaunch of every",
    "in-flight session."
  ],
  "version": 1,
  "tiers": {
    "cheap": ["claude-haiku-4-5-20251001"],
    "standard": ["claude-sonnet-4-6"],
    "deep": ["claude-opus-4-1", "claude-sonnet-4-6"]
  },
  "defaultTier": "standard",
  "routes": [
    { "when": { "task_tag": "world_model_distill" }, "tier": "cheap" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "capsule_compile" }, "tier": "cheap" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "summarise" }, "tier": "cheap" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "claim_lowering" }, "tier": "cheap" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "discovery" }, "tier": "standard" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "judge" }, "tier": "standard" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "planning" }, "tier": "deep" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "agent_turn" }, "tier": "standard" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "agent_turn", "stage": "design" }, "tier": "deep" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "agent_turn", "stage": "develop" }, "tier": "deep" },
    { "when": { "task_tag": "agent_turn", "stage": "fix" }, "tier": "deep" }
  ],
  "escalateWhenInputTokensExceed": {
    "cheap": 60000,
    "standard": 150000
  }
}
